HEADWORD: oilrig
<hw>oil"rig`</hw></mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A
structure and associated machinery used in drilling for oil or gas; it
is usually in the form of a tower. Called also <altname>drilling
rig</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> drill rig, drilling rig, oil rig.</syn>⟦br⟧
